properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued January 13 at 2:56PM CST until January 14 at 9:00AM CST by NWS Duluth MN
properties.description:
...ACCUMULATING SNOW EXPECTED THIS EVENING THROUGH TUESDAY
MORNING...

.A potent, but fast-moving, system will pass through the region
this evening through Tuesday morning, which will bring some
widespread accumulating snow to the Northland. The heaviest snow
is anticipated to fall along the North Shore tonight, thanks to
lake enhanced snowfall due to persistent southerly winds.
Additionally, heavier snowfall amounts are expected from
Koochiching County into northern St. Louis county. Some freezing
drizzle may mix in at times during the early morning hours
Tuesday, but snow will be the primary threat.

* WHAT...Snow expected. Total snow accumulations of 1 to 4
inches.

* WHERE...Koochiching and North St. Louis Counties. This
includes the Tribal Lands of the Bois Forte Band, Nett Lake
area.

* WHEN...From 9 PM this evening to 9 AM CST Tuesday.

* IMPACTS...Plan on slippery road conditions. The hazardous
conditions could impact the morning commute.
properties.instruction:
Slow down and use caution while traveling.

The latest road conditions can be obtained by calling 5 1 1.
Road conditions can also be found at 511mn.org for Minnesota or
511wi.gov for Wisconsin.

NWSheadline: WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY IN EFFECT FROM 9 PM THIS EVENING TO 9 AM CST TUESDAY
